Malawi’s Benchmark Tea Price Falls 15% at Sale Yesterday, Tea Brokers Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-06-08T06:33:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/malawi-s-benchmark-tea-price-falls-15-at-sale-yesterday-tea-brokers-says.html
The benchmark price of tea in  Malawi ,
 Africa ’s largest producer of the crop after Kenya, fell 15
percent to $1.88 per kilogram (2.2 pounds) at an auction
yesterday, Tea Brokers Central Africa, which manages the
country’s tea auctions, said in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  